{
  "stem": "7458.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were talking about market days and the violence that quite often occurred on market days in form of a pogrom.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I recall such days.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Of course, the object was to get out of their way, to hide, until the drunken farmers would leave town and life would begin to be normal again.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Unfortunately, quite often, those violent outbursts were led by the priest, or clergy, who, by and large, were uneducated drunkards.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And occasionally, on Polish holidays, they would have processions where they would march with their icons through the streets.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were of the belief that any Jew who shows up in town, or who walks in the same street, violates their holiday.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that would be occasion for a pogrom, occasionally.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Also, around Passover, there was always the fear of those horrible, wild, unfounded accusations.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was called the blood [INAUDIBLE] about the-- the legend that Jewish people use Christian children's blood for baking matzah.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was, quite often, the occasion for a pogrom.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not I, personally, but my town, yes, there were such accusations.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes, I did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not from pogroms that I can recall, although I know that there were fights.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By the time, in the 1930s, because [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] socialism came into town and workers were organized, not based on religious affiliation but rather, on the working class-- class versus the capitalist class, then [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Jews began to arm themselves with weapons, and to protect themselves against such pogroms.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But that was just in the late 1930s, soon before the war began.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I very clearly remember my oldest sisters-- two of my sister's married two brothers, by the name of Bailach, Chaim and Avremel Bailach.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
